!. How to run

Rscript run_agent.R --app application.yaml --scoring scoring.yaml --targets targets.csv --out output

Outputs:

output/ranked_targets.csv

output/ranked_targets.json

output/bundles/*.json (one per target, full audit trail)

2. What to add immediately after MVP (to make it much better without changing the design)

   2.1 Add TCGA genetic evidence (1–2 days)
       Use TCGAbiolinks to pull mutation/CNA prevalence in LUAD/LUSC and compute:
	prevalence
	enrichment in EGFR-mut subgroup (where possible)
	Wire those metrics into bundle$metrics → update genetic_evidence bins.

   2.2 Add DepMap essentiality + context dependency (2–3 days)
       Pull dependency scores for LUAD lines with EGFR features.
       Use it to improve:
	genetic evidence (functional essentiality)
	toxicity risk (essentiality across many lineages)

   2.3 Add “context match” logic (1 day)
       Right now, trials/papers are “target + disease + context terms”. You can improve trust by:
	parsing for co-mentions (osimertinib AND “primary resistance”)
	downweighting “adjacent” evidence (e.g., 2L or non-EGFR NSCLC)

3. Important note about “trustworthy” scoring in MVP
   Some categories (especially toxicity risk and genetic evidence) are placeholders unless you integrate essentiality/normal tissue expression/KO phenotype and cohort/TCGA data. The MVP structure is designed so you can plug those in without changing the workflow.
